                <li>When we provide you with services, products or support,</li>
                <li>When you browse or use our website, e-commerce services or social networking pages.</li>",
    'paragraph6' => "The purposes for which we collect and use your personal data may vary depending on the type of relationship you have with us, for example if you are one of our employees, customers or a user of the website. The Company always collects and uses personal data according to the purpose limitation principle.",
    'list6' => "<li><strong>Employees and candidates :</strong> if you apply for a job, we use your personal data to consider your recruitment and to manage your account. If you have an employment or business relationship with the Company, we use your personal data to develop our contractual relationship, to conduct performance reviews and to comply with legal obligations, including tax and social security regulations.</li>
                <li><strong>Customers :</strong> we use customer information to maintain our business relationships, to ensure the smooth operation of day-to-day business, to comply with tax and other regulations and to manage sales and marketing activities.</li>
                <li><strong>Clients of our customers :</strong> if necessary we provide support services to customers who use health products and services.</li>
                <li><strong>Potential clients :</strong> information from potential customers is used to respond to their requests for information, products or services and for sales and marketing activities.</li>
                <li><strong>Suppliers :</strong> if you have a business or professional relationship with the Company, we use your personal data to develop our business relationship and to comply with tax and other regulations.</li>
                <li><strong>Visitors to our sites (offices and agencies) and event venues :</strong> some premises are equipped with physical access controls and video surveillance systems for security purposes.</li>
                <li><strong>Website and social network users :</strong> we collect personal data from visitors and users of our website and social networking pages. We use the information to manage your account registration, store your preferences and settings, provide targeted advertising based on your interests, compile statistics and analyze your behavior with respect to our website and online services.</li>",
    'paragraph6bis' => "The Company may use the personal data of its employees, customers, potential customers, vendors or suppliers for other purposes based on its legitimate interests such as: to analyze the purchasing behavior of certain products, for product development, to create statistics on customer loyalty, to create profiles prior to the introduction of a service offering.",
    'paragraph7' => "<strong>The Company only collects and uses personal data where there is a lawful and fair basis for its collection and use, for example, where it is necessary to enter into a contract, to satisfy our legitimate interests, to comply with legal obligations or where we have your consent.</strong>
                    </br></br>
                    The information we collect when we enter into a contract or business relationship with you is, unless otherwise specified, necessary to develop contractual relationships and to comply with legal obligations. For example, certain tax, labor, anti-fraud, anti-corruption or compliance laws require organizations to collect certain information that may vary depending on local regulations. Without the necessary information required, we would not be able to work with you.
                    </br></br>
                    Marketing activities are generally based on your consent or an existing business relationship with the Company. However, you may unsubscribe from these communications at any time and free of charge.
                    </br></br>
                    When we use your personal data for our legitimate interests, we always carry out a balancing of interests to ensure that the data subject's rights are maintained and respected.
                    </br></br>
                    Finally, when we have access to personal data on behalf of our customers as a subcontractor, a written contract regulates the service and, in particular, the specific instructions concerning the processing of the data and their safeguarding.",
    'paragraph8' => "The Company applies the storage time limitation principle to keep personal data in our files only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose for which the data was collected. We do not keep personal data longer than necessary, and what is necessary depends on the specific circumstances, such as regulations requiring information to be kept for a specific period of time or statutes of limitations for legal disputes.",
    'paragraph9' => "<strong>The Company sometimes uses third parties, contractors, service providers and other suppliers to assist it in achieving its business objectives. There are other circumstances in which the Company is required by law to disclose personal data to third parties, such as government agencies or legal authorities.</strong>
                    </br></br>
                    If third party engagements involve the transmission of personal data, the Company requires the service provider to handle such data in accordance with this policy. A data protection agreement must be in place before the data is disclosed.
                    </br></br>
                    In certain circumstances, the Company may be required to disclose personal information when required by law, when necessary to protect our rights or in an emergency situation where the health or safety of an individual is threatened.
                    </br></br>
                    We may also disclose personal data in connection with a sale or transaction involving all or part of the business.",
    'paragraph10' => "<strong>The Company is committed to the principles of security, confidentiality and integrity. We take all commercially reasonable precautions to protect personal data in our possession from unauthorized access and use and we periodically review our security measures. We are committed to handling your data securely and have specific technical and organizational measures in place to prevent accidental or deliberate compromise of the personal data we hold.</strong>
                    </br></br>
                    The Company uses<strong><i>VeriSign</i></strong> for the security certificates for its sites. Please note that these safeguards do not protect information that is not collected through our website, such as information provided to us via e-mail.
                    </br></br>
                    We conduct risk assessments, ensure that our employees understand the importance of protecting personal data, and responsibly manage access rights within the company. We include both physical and IT security in our overall approach to data security. We are vigilant in selecting suppliers who process personal data on our behalf to ensure that they take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the data.
                    </br></br>
                    The Company makes reasonable efforts to notify individuals and regulatory authorities, as required by law, of situations where we have reasonable grounds to believe that personal information has been stolen, disclosed, altered or otherwise compromised by an unauthorized person. We create and maintain a notification and reporting protocol.
                    </br></br>
                    The Company also applies the concept of Privacy by Design, which is an approach to project management that promotes privacy and data protection compliance from the outset. This means considering privacy and security impacts for any new project or process throughout its life cycle.",
    'paragraph11' => "<strong>If you reside or are located in the European territory, the Company undertakes to facilitate the exercise of your rights under European data protection law. In this case, you can <a href='#14'><u>contact us</u></a> at any time to discuss your privacy concerns.</strong>
                    </br></br>
                    <strong><u>The right to privacy under the European Regulation :</u></strong>
                    </br>",
    'div11' => "<strong>Transparency and right to information :</strong> we inform employees, customers, suppliers, vendors and others of how we use personal data in their day-to-day activities at the time of collection or as soon as possible thereafter. We also publish this privacy notice for greater transparency.",
    'div11bis' => "<strong>Right of access, rectification, limitation of data processing and right to be forgotten :</strong> we provide data subjects with access to their own personal data when required by law. In addition, we rectify their personal data when it is incorrect and inaccurate, and we guarantee the right to be forgotten and the right to restrict processing when these rights are not compatible with local regulations.",
    'div11ter' => "<strong>Right to object and withdraw consent at any time :</strong> for marketing materials, you may unsubscribe at any time and free of charge. The right to object to further processing activities must be balanced to ensure that it is not incompatible with local regulations or the legitimate interests of the Company.",
    'div11quater' => "<strong>Right to data portability :</strong> depending on your particular situation, we grant data subjects the right to obtain and reuse their data in various services and this includes the transfer of data to the data subject, another data controller or a trusted third party.",
